The geographer Pomponius Mela 111. 1 1 says Nzgrritarum Gaetularmnque passim vagantium ne litora quidem infecunda sunt purpura et murice efficacissimis ad tingendum. The island os Girba (inodernJerbah) or Meninx, as it was earlier called, lies to the south-east of the Lesser Syrtis. The Lotophagi were said to have lived there: but it was not near the territory occupied in historic times by the Gaetulians, who extended to the sea only to the S.W. of Mauretania.
